{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4f2048ed-0c54-44ef-b190-de9781171026","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform the CLI flags change. The equivalent is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project <TestProject> -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/**/[Category=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n\n| VSTest (`dotnet test`) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/**/[Category=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to the test project):\n\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\n> **Note:** On .NET 8 there's no `dotnet test` integration with MTP — you must use `dotnet run --project ... --` (or invoke the built executable directly). The `dotnet test` bridge (`--testsuite mtp`) requires the .NET 9+ SDK.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8957a974-af75-4b03-9755-369421fdee95","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`(same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` (with Microsoft.CodeCoverage) or you use a different mechanism\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nThe command structure shifts from `dotnet test` to running the test executable directly, though with .NET 9 SDK and later, `dotnet test` gains native support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform through the `--testsuite mtp` flag.\n\nFor .NET 8 specifically, when migrating to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the CLI arguments map differently: `--filter` may need adjustment depending on the adapter, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`, `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` converts to `--coverage` with the Microsoft.CodeCoverage package, and `--blame-crash` maps to `--crashdump`.\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, you'd run the test executable directly or use `dotnet run --project <path>` with the MTP arguments, since `--testsuite mtp` is a .NET 9+ SDK feature. A practical command would pass flags like `--treenode-filter` for filtering, `--report-trx` for test results, `--coverage` with output format specification, and dump options like `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` with timeout configuration. actually, the key thing is that with .NET 8 and Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you run the test executable directly and the flag names change—things like `--filter` become `--treenode-filter`, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`, and coverage/crash/hang diagnostics require their respective extension packages to be referenced in the project.","outputTokens":1573,"requestId":"4C1A:188DB0:D112B4:105554E:6A0129C1"},"id":"3b31af1b-9099-467e-b347-dd14cf4d62a2","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:59:08.018Z","parentId":"2876d8a7-71db-4934-ab2d-2430cd2258f7"}
